TV Journalist Jacque Maribe’s employer, ROYAL MEDIA SERVICES (RMS)  has Issued a statement calling for her release. In a letter to probation officers, Group Managing Director Wachira Waruru expressed confidence that the Citizen TV journalist would adhere to bail conditions if released. “Having engaged her for the last six years and assessing her performance, we hereby vouch for her character and recommend for her admission to bail,” read part of the statement. RMS further confirmed that Maribe is still an employee of the media house and had taken leave to attend to personal issues. This comes a day after Maribe and her co-accused Joseph Kuria Irungu alias Jowie pleaded not guilty to fresh charges read out to them and will discover on Tuesday if their bail application is successful.  